11/04/2010
 BELGRADE, Serbia -- A 25-year-old man died on Friday (April 9th) in Belgrade after activating a hand grenade in a taxi. Jovan Kostic allegedly hijacked the taxi by threatening the driver with a gun. After a police chase in which gunfire was exchanged, the man activated the grenade. The driver managed to get out of the taxi just before the explosion. Kostic died in a Belgrade hospital. While the reason for the hijacking remains unknown, police later found a large amount of guns and explosives in Kostic's apartment. (B92, FoNet, RTS - 10/04/10) 
